The paper discusses a machine learning model for predicting time-varying distributions with limited training data. This task involves regression and time series analysis, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and statistics and data analysis (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
